CORE MECHANICS & SYSTEMS\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0 \cf2 \ul \outl0\strokewidth-182 Traversal\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone \outl0\strokewidth-182 Forward movement is automatic. Moving side to side (and potentially up and down is up to the player). Side to side movement is enacted by dragging the biker to the right or left. Full range of motion from right to left is allowed. \
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ul \outl0\strokewidth-182 \
Player Health\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone \outl0\strokewidth-182 The player has a certain amount of HP. When they take damage, that HP goes down. When that HP goes down to 0, it\'92s Game Over for the player.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ul \outl0\strokewidth-182 \
Shooting\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone \outl0\strokewidth-182 By tapping on certain on-screen objects (enemies and perhaps specific obstacle types) the player can shoot their weapon in the direction of their tap. Certain constraints need to be placed on this mechanic (otherwise, the player could just snipe everything from a distance). An obvious constraint is ammo. Another might be the need to hold down a tap for longer to take aim or launch a powerful projectile. Another still might be an enemy type that is impervious to this kind of attack.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ul \outl0\strokewidth-182 \
Sword Strike\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone \outl0\strokewidth-182 In certain circumstances, the player can slash at their enemies. The player can also use their sword to deflect incoming projectiles. Constraints need to be applied to this form of attack as well, for the same reasons as above. \
\
As for controls, the sword can be drawn by pressing an onscreen button. The player can then slash with it by tapping the appropriate object or enemy. \
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ul \outl0\strokewidth-182 \
Power-Ups\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone \outl0\strokewidth-182 Throughout the course of play, the player can pick up certain objects that grant them additional abilities or buffs. For example, the player may obtain a temporary invincibility power up or an upgrade to their bike or weapons.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 \outl0\strokewidth-182 \
ENEMIES\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0 \cf2 \outl0\strokewidth-182 Before designing a whole stable of interesting and discrete enemies, we must first drill down into the 
\f1\i \outl0\strokewidth-182 categories 
\f2\i0 \outl0\strokewidth-182 the enemies will come to occupy. Once these categories are explicated, a single archetype for each category should be designed\'97in broad strokes\'97and then implemented in-game. \
\
There are two good places to start vis a vis these categories: ranged and close-quarter.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ul \outl0\strokewidth-182 Ranged \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone \outl0\strokewidth-182 These enemies approach from in front of the player and hold their distance so that they can launch a ranged attack. \
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ul \outl0\strokewidth-182 \
Close-quarter\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone \outl0\strokewidth-182 These enemies can approach from in front of the player or from back-left or back-right (in relation to the player) in order to attack with a melee weapon or their vehicle itself. \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 \outl0\strokewidth-182 \
WORLD GENERATION\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0 \cf2 \outl0\strokewidth-182 The environment in CYBERBIKER is procedurally generated. This means that every run is different than the last. \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 \outl0\strokewidth-182 \
OBSTACLES, INTERACTABLES, & PICKUPS\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0 \cf2 \outl0\strokewidth-182 Combat is one half of the challenge coin in CYBERBIKER. The player must also contend with the act of traversal itself (such is the nature of most endless runners). Since forward movement in CYBERBIKER is automatic, side-to-side directional control and interaction with the game environment are the main concerns for the player. \
\
As with enemies, creating a series of categories or buckets to use as guiding principles for design and implementation is key when it comes to this aspect of the game. To that end, the three categories to consider are:\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ul \outl0\strokewidth-182 Obstacles\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone \outl0\strokewidth-182 Simply put, these are objects that must be avoided by the player. Coming into contact with them will damage the player, thereby reducing HP.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ul \outl0\strokewidth-182 \
Interactables\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone \outl0\strokewidth-182 These are objects that the player can interact with in certain ways, usually to their benefit. For example, a boost pad (the player drives over them to receive a speed increase that allows them to smash through objects or jump longer distances) or a ramp (the player drives over them to reach higher areas). \
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ul \outl0\strokewidth-182 \
Pickups\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone \outl0\strokewidth-182 More often than not, a power-up, but can also include things like ammo or additional health. These pickups can be obtained by running into them with the bike, but sometimes they need to be shot (if they are out of physical range).\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 \outl0\strokewidth-182 \
DIFFICULTY & PROGRESSION\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0 \cf2 \outl0\strokewidth-182 It is not enough that the player simply navigate obstacles and fight enemies. The level of challenge these actions present must increase with 
\f1\i \outl0\strokewidth-182 time
\f2\i0 \outl0\strokewidth-182 . As the game progresses, the reaction time required by the player must narrow, new challenges must be introduced, and additional complexity must be introduced.\
\
It stands to reason then that as challenge increases so too does the potential for rewards. This is to be reflected in the player\'92s score and the various rewards the player may encounter during their play through (currency, achievements, and so forth). \
\
As what \'93shape\'94 this challenge progression will take, that will be revealed through careful testing and balancing. But the variables required to increase that difficulty must be made available in-engine before that testing and balancing can begin. A good place to start is player speed (more on this 
\f0\b \outl0\strokewidth-182 MVP
\f2\b0 \outl0\strokewidth-182 ).\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 \outl0\strokewidth-182 SCORING\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0 \cf2 \outl0\strokewidth-182 Much like the shape/curve of challenge and progression, the \'93equation\'94 used to determine a player\'92s score will be tested and iterated on over time. \
\
To begin with, score must accrue at a base rate with time (meaning, if 
\f1\i \outl0\strokewidth-182 all 
\f2\i0 \outl0\strokewidth-182 the player did was travel in a straight line\'97if such a thing were possible\'97they would simply be rewarded for 
\f1\i \outl0\strokewidth-182 existing). \
\

\f2\i0 \outl0\strokewidth-182 On top of this base layer, we will then need to add points for successfully navigating obstacles, defeating enemies, and pulling off difficult maneuvers or finding secrets. And on and on this list will go as new features are developed\'85\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 \outl0\strokewidth-182 \
MONETIZATION & IN-GAME SHOP\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0 \cf2 \outl0\strokewidth-182 The player will pick up in-game currency (IGC) during their run. They can also be awarded IGC after having completed a run. Finally, they can purchase ICG directly through the game\'92s cash shop.\
\
As to what IGC will be spent on, there are of course many options, but as with many things we\'92ve gone over above, there are broad categories to consider.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ul \outl0\strokewidth-182 Non-Competitive Benefits\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone \outl0\strokewidth-182 These purchasable items do not affect the player\'92s performance. They will most likely be cosmetic in nature (new skins, for example).\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ul \outl0\strokewidth-182 \
Competitive Benefits\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone \outl0\strokewidth-182 These purchasable items will give the player an edge in some way. For example, the player may purchase a resurrection in the shop that will activate upon death in-game, allowing them to continue their run.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 \outl0\strokewidth-182 \
ACHIEVEMENTS\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0 \cf2 \outl0\strokewidth-182 With \'93simple\'94 mobile games that have relatively short runtimes, it is important to encourage return visits to the game. Of course, high scores are one way to do this. Another is a robust achievement system.\
\
Not only are achievements a \'93cheap\'94 way to reward the player for engaging with the game in a deeper way (you\'92ve killed 1 enemy, now try 5), they also encourage the player to experiment or discover new parts of the game (use a ramp to reach the upper level of the game\'92s environment).\
